race.comment: KILBRANNAN (8) underrated colt desperate for this trip and further. Held in high regard by the stable and was a total forgive when returned from a let-up over the unsuitable 1200m at Warwick Farm. Berry sticks from the good gate and is closely related to Fireburn and Kintyre. Go close. STARPHISTOCATED (6) tongue-tie goes on third-up and she doesn't have to improve much to win this. Did a stack of work in the run with a fighting second over 1600m at Randwick in this class. Can slide across from the draw and hold a forward position. Top-three player. ICEMAN (3) bounced off the two good trials with an eye-catching effort from back in the field to finish second over 1350m at this track first-up. Will come on for this and looks set for a big campaign. EMBRACE THE WIND (9) big jump in class after winning his last two in good style at the provincials. Zac Lloyd goes on from the sticky gate and should get the trip.
